wiki.content: On December 2, 2023, Ken Carson took to Instagram Live to preview a 34-second snippet of “Breathe.” On December 10, 2023, rumored Opium signee L5 previewed the song again, with the caption “Breathe.” Later, on January 7, 2024, Ken tweeted “LON-PAR-AMS” referring to the line ‘London, Paris, Amsterdam, yeah, I’m overseas.’ He then quickly deleted the tweet. One month later, on February 8th 2024, Ken tweeted “vdayorbday”, teasing a potential release for either Valentine’s day or his birthday, April 11th On April 1, 2024, Ken would take to his alternate Instagram account (@agreatchaos) to announce the release of the song on April 11, 2024, which is also Ken’s birthday. Finally, on April 11th 2024, the song released at 5 PM PST on all streaming services. "overseas" debuted at #57 on the Global Spotify Charts, marking Ken's first single to do so. The song also racked in over 2 million streams on Spotify alone in its first 24 hours of being out. Read more on Last.fm.
